According to the ''[[Nihon Shoki]]'', he was the son of [[Emperor Kōrei]].<ref>Louis-Frédéric, [https://books.google.com/books?id=p2QnPijAEmEC&pg=PA513&dq= "Kibitsu-hiko no Mikoto"] in ''Japan Encyclopedia'', p. 513.</ref> Legend says this prince slayed an ogre called Ura, which may be the demonization of the [[Kingdom of Kibi]], destroyed during the reign of Kōrei-Tennō.
His ''[[kami]]'' is enshrined at [[Shinto shrine]]s in [[Kibitsu Shrine (Bitchū)|Okayama Prefecture]] and [[Kibitsu Shrine (Bingo)|Hiroshima Prefecture]].<ref>Kotodamaya.com, [http://www.kotodamaya.com/kibitsuhiko-jinja/ Kibitsuhiko jinja]; [http://www.kotodamaya.com/kibitsu-jinja-bingo/ Kibitsu jinja (Bingo)]; [http://www.kotodamaya.com/kibitsu-jinja/ Kibitsu jinja (Bitchu)]; retrieved 2012-11-20.</ref>
